      "version": "0.1.0+canvas-refresh-and-skills-picker",
      "status": "shipped",
      "description": "Operator created 'Taylor Grift' agent (likely from the Agents tab or Chat tab) and it didn't appear in the Canvas Conversations palette — the palette only loaded its agents list once at canvas-page construction. Fixed by overriding CanvasPage.showEvent to call palette.reload_agents() every time the operator navigates to the Canvas tab. Cheap (single agents.list RPC); fires only on tab switch. Also shipped a multi-select Skills picker (per the operator's request 'set skills for the agent per model and select them'): new skills.list RPC scans ~/.claude/skills/ for Claude; new SkillsPicker dialog wired to a 'Browse skills…' button on Chat tab + Canvas New-Conversation dialog.",
      "change_overview": [
        "apps/gui/canvas/page.py — CanvasPage.showEvent overrides Qt's default to fire palette.reload_agents() on every tab visit",
        "apps/service/main.py — new skills_list RPC scanning ~/.claude/skills/*.md; description picked from front-matter description: or first non-empty body line",
        "apps/service/main.py — _first_descriptive_line helper",
        "apps/service/main.py — server.register('skills.list', h.skills_list)",
        "apps/gui/widgets/skills_picker.py — SkillsPicker QDialog with multi-select list + pre-checked from current /tokens; selected_tokens() returns /name1 /name2",
        "apps/gui/windows/chat.py — Browse skills… button next to Skills field; _open_skills_picker splices picked tokens with any free-form text",
        "apps/gui/canvas/palette.py — Browse… button on the New-Conversation dialog Skills row; same splice behaviour",
        "apps/gui/ipc/client.py — _friendlier wraps RpcClient errors so 'unknown method: X' surfaces a 'run scripts/restart.cmd' hint instead of cryptic raw text"
      ],
      "risk_level": "Low",
      "risk_note": "showEvent override calls super first; reload is idempotent and async (won't block tab switch). SkillsPicker is a brand-new file used only by the new buttons. The friendlier-error wrapper only modifies error messages — no behaviour change for success paths.",
      "next_steps": [
        "Run scripts/restart.cmd so the service picks up the new skills.list RPC registration",
        "Click any other tab then return to Canvas — the palette should refresh; create an agent in the Agents tab and watch it appear in the canvas Conversations list on next canvas visit"
      ],
