      "status": "no_change_needed",
      "description": "Operator saw 'Reload failed: unknown method: blueprints.list' on the Blueprints tab. The friendlier-error wrapper from PR #19 (apps/gui/ipc/client.py:_friendlier) is already firing the correct hint: 'service is running an older code version than the GUI. Run scripts\\restart.cmd…' This is the intended diagnostic surface for the post-merge stale-service case (Phase 6 added blueprints.* and drones.* RPCs that an old service process won't know). No GUI code change can fix the underlying mismatch — the operator must restart the service so it picks up the new RPC registrations.",
      "change_overview": [
        "No code change for annotation #9 itself.",
        "Bundled in this attempt: scripts/start.cmd, scripts/test-claude.cmd, scripts/test-gemini.cmd, scripts/limits.cmd, scripts/doctor.cmd — every bare `claude` / `gemini` invocation now goes through `call …` so cmd.exe doesn't tail-call out of the script (operator hit this earlier: pre-flight printed `claude --version` then exited without ever probing Gemini or launching the GUI; doctor.cmd had the same bug — `where claude && claude --version` would have bailed before the port / data-dir / annotator / version sections)."
      ],
